<subSubSection id="5DA66552FFC9FFC306A2FA93FA0CF8B9" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" type="key">
<keyStep id="AE482E7CFFC9FFC306A2FA93FA0CFA6F" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2FA93FA0CFAAA" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" box="[151,1436,1336,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2FA93FA0CFAAA" box="[151,1436,1336,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
1 Pronotum without black spots (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC3043BFA93FDD8FAA9" box="[526,584,1336,1358]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1224,1248]" captionTargetBox="[218,1347,196,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[151,1435,181,1200]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Gonioctena lukasi new species, male holotype. 3: dorsal habitus, 4: lateral habitus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610115" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610115/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); elytral striae in single rows of punctures, partially irregular.................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2FAFDFA0CFA6F" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2FAFDFA0CFA6F" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
- Pronotum with nine black spots, rarely enlarged and connected (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC30570FAFEFC11FA8C" box="[837,897,1365,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1224,1248]" captionTargetBox="[207,1347,193,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[151,1435,181,1200]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Gonioctena jolantae new species, male holotype. 1: dorsal habitus, 2: lateral habitus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610113/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC305B8FAFEFC22FA8C" box="[909,946,1365,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1144]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[151,1435,181,1144]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Dorsal habitus. 5: Gonioctena kamikawai (Chûjô, 1958) 6: G. fujiana Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610117/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">5, 6</figureCitation>
); elytral strial punctures entirely confused single or double rows......................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="AE482E7CFFC9FFC306A2FA3BFA0DF9DE" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2FA3BFA0DFA07" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2FA3BFA0DFA07" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
2 Median lobe in dorsal view constricted in middle and abruptly before apex to an approximately triangular process with slightly expanded tip (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC3075CFA06FE32FA23" box="[361,418,1453,1476]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,465,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-114@7.[151,1436,453,1721]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Gonioctena species, male genitalia. 7: G. jolantae new species (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 8: G. lukasi new species (dorsal &amp; lateral), 9: G. kanfani (Chen, 1941) (apico-dorsal &amp; lateral, redrawn from Yang et al. 2014), 10: G. kamikawai (Chûjô, 1958) (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 11: G. fujiana Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610119/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), in lateral view apical half abruptly enlarged but with thin curved apical process; body length 
<quantity id="D2449B3CFFC9FFC30316FA06FA08FA24" box="[1315,1432,1453,1475]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="6.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" unit="mm" value="7.35" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="6.4">6.4–8.3 mm</quantity>
; 
<collectingCountry id="6DAB7649FFC9FFC306D7FA60FE8BFA06" box="[226,283,1483,1505]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="D778F83BFFC9FFC3071DFA60FE11FA06" box="[296,385,1483,1505]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
).................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFC9FFC302FFFA60FAB0FA07" authority="Cho, 2022" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[1226,1312,1483,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukasi" status="new species">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC302FFFA60FB4BFA07" box="[1226,1243,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC302D2FA60FAB0FA07" box="[1255,1312,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">lukasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC30313FA60FA0DFA07" bold="true" box="[1318,1437,1482,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3CFB57B0FFC9FFC30313FA60FA0DFA07" box="[1318,1437,1482,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2FA42FA0DF9DE" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2FA42FA0DF9DE" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
- Median lobe in dorsal view long, thin and parallel-sided then gradually contracted almost to slightly expanded apical process (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC306DCF9AEFEB3F9FB" box="[233,291,1541,1564]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,465,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-114@7.[151,1436,453,1721]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Gonioctena species, male genitalia. 7: G. jolantae new species (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 8: G. lukasi new species (dorsal &amp; lateral), 9: G. kanfani (Chen, 1941) (apico-dorsal &amp; lateral, redrawn from Yang et al. 2014), 10: G. kamikawai (Chûjô, 1958) (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 11: G. fujiana Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610119/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), in lateral view entirely thin and moderately curved with apical process thinner and recurved; body length 
<quantity id="D2449B3CFFC9FFC30316F9ADFA08F9FC" box="[1315,1432,1542,1563]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.95" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="7.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" unit="mm" value="7.95" valueMax="8.8" valueMin="7.1">7.1–8.8 mm</quantity>
; 
<collectingCountry id="6DAB7649FFC9FFC306D7F988FE8BF9DE" box="[226,283,1571,1593]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="D778F83BFFC9FFC3071DF988FEF8F9DE" box="[296,360,1571,1593]" country="China" name="Anhui" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Anhui</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="D778F83BFFC9FFC30744F988FE58F9DE" box="[369,456,1571,1593]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
)................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFC9FFC302DBF988FA0DF9DE" authority="(Chen)" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[1262,1437,1571,1593]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanfani">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC302DBF988FB6FF9DF" box="[1262,1279,1571,1592]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC30339F988FAC4F9DF" box="[1292,1364,1571,1592]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">kanfani</emphasis>
(Chen)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="AE482E7CFFC9FFC306A2F9EBFA0CF94A" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2F9EBFA0CF994" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2F9EBFA0CF994" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
3 Larger, body length 
<quantity id="D2449B3CFFC9FFC30796F9EBFD89F9B1" box="[419,537,1600,1622]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.35" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="7.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" unit="mm" value="8.35" valueMax="8.9" valueMin="7.8">7.8–8.9 mm</quantity>
; median lobe in dorsal view parallel-sided with apical process slightly broader than shaft (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC30340F9EBFF6BF993" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,465,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-114@7.[151,1436,453,1721]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Gonioctena species, male genitalia. 7: G. jolantae new species (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 8: G. lukasi new species (dorsal &amp; lateral), 9: G. kanfani (Chen, 1941) (apico-dorsal &amp; lateral, redrawn from Yang et al. 2014), 10: G. kamikawai (Chûjô, 1958) (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 11: G. fujiana Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610119/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry id="6DAB7649FFC9FFC3073BF9F6FED7F994" box="[270,327,1629,1651]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="D778F83BFFC9FFC30766F9F6FE04F994" box="[339,404,1629,1651]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fujian</collectingRegion>
)............................................................. ... 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFC9FFC302A4F9F5FA0CF994" authority="Cho &amp; Borowiec" authorityName="Cho &amp; Borowiec" authorityYear="2016" box="[1169,1436,1629,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiana">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC302A4F9F5FB32F994" box="[1169,1186,1630,1651]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFC9FFC3029BF9F6FB62F995" box="[1198,1266,1629,1650]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">fujiana</emphasis>
Cho &amp; Borowiec
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2F9D0FA0CF94A" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2F9D0FA0CF94A" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
- Smaller, body length 
<quantity id="D2449B3CFFC9FFC30784F9D0FDB8F977" box="[433,552,1659,1681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.699999999999999" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="112" unit="mm" value="6.699999999999999" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="5.6">5.6–7.8 mm</quantity>
; median lobe in dorsal view subparallel-sided with a distinct constriction before apical process, which is narrower than median lobe shaft (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC30485F933FC81F949" box="[688,785,1688,1710]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,465,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-114@7.[151,1436,453,1721]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Gonioctena species, male genitalia. 7: G. jolantae new species (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 8: G. lukasi new species (dorsal &amp; lateral), 9: G. kanfani (Chen, 1941) (apico-dorsal &amp; lateral, redrawn from Yang et al. 2014), 10: G. kamikawai (Chûjô, 1958) (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 11: G. fujiana Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610119/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Figs 7, 10</figureCitation>
).................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="AE482E7CFFC9FFC306A2F91DFA0CF8B9" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFC9FFC306A2F91DFA0DF8E1" blockId="1.[151,1437,1336,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
<keyLead id="AE4D95ECFFC9FFC306A2F91DFA0DF8E1" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">
4 Irregularly outlined yellowish-brown markings on elytral humeri extend across 3/5 of elytral base (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC30282F91EFB61F92B" box="[1207,1265,1717,1740]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1224,1248]" captionTargetBox="[207,1347,193,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[151,1435,181,1200]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Gonioctena jolantae new species, male holotype. 1: dorsal habitus, 2: lateral habitus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610113/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); median lobe in dorsal view with apical process rounded laterally (
<figureCitation id="8D872A5CFFC9FFC304F9F978FC98F90F" box="[716,776,1747,1769]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,465,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-114@7.[151,1436,453,1721]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Gonioctena species, male genitalia. 7: G. jolantae new species (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 8: G. lukasi new species (dorsal &amp; lateral), 9: G. kanfani (Chen, 1941) (apico-dorsal &amp; lateral, redrawn from Yang et al. 2014), 10: G. kamikawai (Chûjô, 1958) (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral), 11: G. fujiana Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (dorsal, apico-dorsal &amp; lateral). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610119/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="112">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), in lateral view less curved; body length 
